<subsection name="Load Data" id="Load">
<p>
To load JSON data files generated by Harvest tool, use <i>load-data</i> command:
</p>

<source>
Usage: registry-manager load-data &lt;options&gt;

Load data into registry index

Required parameters:
  -file &lt;path&gt;    A JSON file or a directory to load.
Optional parameters:
  -auth &lt;file&gt;    Authentication config file
  -es &lt;url&gt;       Elasticsearch URL. Default is http://localhost:9200
  -index &lt;name&gt;   Elasticsearch index name. Default is 'registry'
</source>

<p>
For example, to load data from <i>/home/pds/harvest/out/es-docs.json</i> file use the following command.
<source>
registry-manager load-data -file /home/pds/harvest/out/es-docs.json
</source>
</p>

</subsection>

